Step 1: Identify the net profit from the income statement.  
• Net Profit = 3,744,117.89  

Step 2: Determine the Owner's Equity at the beginning and at the end from the balance sheet.  
• Beginning Owner's Equity (2023-12-31) = 28,000,000.00  
• Ending Owner's Equity (2024-02-05) = 31,744,117.89  

Step 3: Calculate the average Owner's Equity for the period.  
• Average Owner's Equity = (28,000,000.00 + 31,744,117.89) / 2  
• Average Owner's Equity = 59,744,117.89 / 2  
• Average Owner's Equity ≈ 29,872,058.945  

Step 4: Compute ROE (Return on Equity) using the formula:  
  ROE = (Net Profit / Average Owner's Equity) × 100  
• ROE = (3,744,117.89 / 29,872,058.945) × 100  
• ROE ≈ 0.1254 × 100  
• ROE ≈ 12.54%

Thus, the Return on Equity (ROE) is approximately 12.54%.
